"{\"uid\": \"ksl.com-article-51079332-how-utah-has-changed-since-hosting-the-2002-olympics\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"To view this video please enable JavaScript, and consider upgrading to a                         web browser thatsupports HTML5 video  Estimated read time: 2-3 minutes  This archived news story is available                                     only for your personal, non-commercial use.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 286, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 33, \"end\": 43, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/JavaScript\", \"score\": 0.9999999993769961, \"rank\": 6.129623092554608e-10, \"text\": \"JavaScript\", \"types\": [\"Q9143\", \"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/JavaScript\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/JavaScript\"}, {\"begin\": 122, \"end\": 133, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/HTML5_video\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"HTML5 video\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/HTML5_video\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/HTML5_video\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Information in the story may be outdated                                     or superseded by additional information.\", \"from\": 287, \"to\": 404, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Reading or replaying the story in its                                     archived form does not constitute a republication of the story.\", \"from\": 405, \"to\": 542, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"SALT LAKE CITY - The last time Utah hosted the Winter Olympics, things looked a little different.\", \"from\": 544, \"to\": 641, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 544, \"end\": 558, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Salt_Lake_City\", \"score\": 0.9999824299283916, \"rank\": 1.3515864925949018e-05, \"text\": \"SALT LAKE CITY\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Salt_Lake_City\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Salt_Lake_City\"}, {\"begin\": 544, \"end\": 558, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Salt_Lake_City\", \"score\": 0.9999824299283916, \"rank\": 1.3515864925949018e-05, \"text\": \"SALT LAKE CITY\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Salt_Lake_City\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Salt_Lake_City\"}, {\"begin\": 575, \"end\": 579, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Utah\", \"score\": 0.9995260701745293, \"rank\": 0.000474123313880532, \"text\": \"Utah\", \"types\": [\"Q3455524\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Utah\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Utah\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"No, we are not just talking about hairstyles or fashion trends.\", \"from\": 643, \"to\": 706, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Back then, there were not nearly as many of us.\", \"from\": 707, \"to\": 754, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"We have added about 1.2 million more people since 2002,\\\" said Natalie Gochnour, who directs the Kem C. Gardner Policy Institute at the University of Utah.\", \"from\": 756, \"to\": 911, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 860, \"end\": 867, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/L._Gardner_and_Sons\", \"score\": 0.7982490664449761, \"rank\": 0.25274183463803657, \"text\": \"Gardner\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/L._Gardner_and_Sons\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/L._Gardner_and_Sons\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"That's about the size of Salt Lake County today.\\\"\", \"from\": 912, \"to\": 962, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 938, \"end\": 954, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Salt_Lake_County,_Utah\", \"score\": 0.9999999999729425, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Salt Lake County\", \"types\": [\"Q3455524\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Salt_Lake_County,_Utah\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Salt_Lake_County,_Utah\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Gochnour said that growth has led to many changes for our once-small state.\", \"from\": 964, \"to\": 1039, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"We have become a larger economy,\\\" she said.\", \"from\": 1041, \"to\": 1085, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"More international trade, more international engagement.\\\"\", \"from\": 1086, \"to\": 1144, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Today Utah acts much bigger.\", \"from\": 1146, \"to\": 1174, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1152, \"end\": 1156, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Utah\", \"score\": 0.9995260701745293, \"rank\": 0.000474123313880532, \"text\": \"Utah\", \"types\": [\"Q3455524\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Utah\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Utah\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Take Salt Lake City, for example.\", \"from\": 1175, \"to\": 1208, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1180, \"end\": 1194, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Salt_Lake_City\", \"score\": 0.9999817423306551, \"rank\": 1.3515864925949018e-05, \"text\": \"Salt Lake City\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Salt_Lake_City\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Salt_Lake_City\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"In 2002, we did not have downtown urban living.\", \"from\": 1210, \"to\": 1258, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"We had a city that closed at 6:00, 7:00 at night,\\\" said Gochnour.\", \"from\": 1259, \"to\": 1324, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Now it's much more of a 24/7 city.\\\"\", \"from\": 1325, \"to\": 1361, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"It's also a city that now has a convention hotel, a Broadway theater, a busy downtown mall, and a brand new international airport.\", \"from\": 1363, \"to\": 1493, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Utah has changed  Utah also has a thriving tech sector, and it's a much bigger tourist destination than it once was.\", \"from\": 1495, \"to\": 1611, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1495, \"end\": 1499, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Utah\", \"score\": 0.9995260701745293, \"rank\": 0.000474123313880532, \"text\": \"Utah\", \"types\": [\"Q3455524\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Utah\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Utah\"}, {\"begin\": 1513, \"end\": 1517, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Utah\", \"score\": 0.9995260701745293, \"rank\": 0.000474123313880532, \"text\": \"Utah\", \"types\": [\"Q3455524\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Utah\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Utah\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"That's thanks to the Olympics, Gochnour said, but also to social media - and the state's \\\"Mighty 5\\\"marketing campaignthat introduced Utah's national parks to the world.\", \"from\": 1612, \"to\": 1780, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1745, \"end\": 1749, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Utah\", \"score\": 0.9995260701745293, \"rank\": 0.000474123313880532, \"text\": \"Utah\", \"types\": [\"Q3455524\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Utah\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Utah\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"A lot has changed in Utah,\\\" she said.\", \"from\": 1782, \"to\": 1820, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1804, \"end\": 1808, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Utah\", \"score\": 0.9995260701745293, \"rank\": 0.000474123313880532, \"text\": \"Utah\", \"types\": [\"Q3455524\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Utah\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Utah\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"And Utah will keep changing before 2034 when the Olympics return.\", \"from\": 1824, \"to\": 1889, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1828, \"end\": 1832, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Utah\", \"score\": 0.9995260701745293, \"rank\": 0.000474123313880532, \"text\": \"Utah\", \"types\": [\"Q3455524\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Utah\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Utah\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Gochnour estimates the state will add another 600,000 people by then, putting us over 4 million in total population.\", \"from\": 1890, \"to\": 2006, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Four out of every 10 Utahns in 2034 will not have been here in 2002,\\\" said Gochnour.\", \"from\": 2008, \"to\": 2093, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Our state has also gotten much more diverse.\", \"from\": 2095, \"to\": 2139, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"In 2002, one in 10 Utahns were an ethnic or racial minority, Gochnour said.\", \"from\": 2140, \"to\": 2215, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"By the time the 2034 Games roll around, it will be nearly one in three.\", \"from\": 2216, \"to\": 2287, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"There is a lot to do to get ready over the next decade.\", \"from\": 2289, \"to\": 2344, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"But Gochnour said it's work that needs to be done anyway to keep up with a state that's changing quickly.\", \"from\": 2345, \"to\": 2450, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"When you are going to be host to the world, you get better in every way,\\\" said Gochnour.\", \"from\": 2452, \"to\": 2541, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I think of the Olympics more as a motivator for the good things we can do for growth that's coming no matter what.\\\"\", \"from\": 2542, \"to\": 2658, \"entities\": []}]}"